The Vice President made a surprise visit to Hampton University in Virginia to speak with students about voting. She highlighted the importance of young voters and their impact on the 2020 election. She also discussed attacks on voting rights in states like Texas and Georgia and emphasized the need to protect and exercise the power to vote. The Vice President mentioned her work on passing the John Lewis Voting Rights Act and the For the People Act to counter restrictions on early voting and expand access to voting methods like vote-by-mail. She encouraged the students to recognize their role as leaders and the significance of their votes in bringing about change.